This paper deals with a communication network and queueing theory, which are both relevant to the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of Poisson arrivals and a common service time suggests a focus on stochastic processes and probability theory, which are also relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The system being analyzed involves preemption, which is a common concept in control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the detour flow graph method, which is a technique used in performance analysis of computer systems (cs.PF). Finally, the analysis of the average age and peak age of each stream suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
